from @KKcorps :
> Can you try to test it in cluster mode while running on a proper YARN, AWS EMR or DataProc cluster.

Good suggestion. I ended up testing this in our YARN environment with success. Although, I have to note that our YARN environment runs Spark 3.0.2 so I had to downgrade Spark version of the connector for the test. Everything else worked as expected.

Steps to reproduce the issue in local:

1. Start upsert quickstart - ` bin/quick-start-upsert-streaming.sh -dataDir $PWD/dataDirUpsert`

2. Create a copy of `conf/pinot-server.conf`. Make the following changes to the new config file -
```properties
pinot.cluster.name=QuickStartCluster
pinot.zk.server=localhost:2123
pinot.server.netty.port=8192
pinot.server.adminapi.port=8193
pinot.server.instance.dataDir=/some/local/dir/dataDirServer2
```

3. Start a second server - `bin/pinot-admin.sh StartServer -configFileName /path/to/pinot-server-copy.conf`

4. Assign a new tenant tag `upsertBugRepro_REALTIME` to this server from UI.

5. Create the following table - 
```json
